    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-duck-curry-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based,<strong> hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-duck-curry-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> tomato[es] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-duck-curry-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the dish is hot, add the<strong> sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>tomato wedges</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong> red Thai curry paste</strong>, 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3/4 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>creamed coconut</strong> and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[260ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> to the dish \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style red curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-duck-curry-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>Thai-style red curry</strong> with your <strong>duck leg[s] </strong>(along with the jelly and fat!) skin-side up and put the dish in the oven, uncovered, for an initial 25 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-duck-curry-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then chop your<strong> green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Cut your <strong>lime[s]</strong> into 2 wedges per person</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-duck-curry-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After 25 min, remove the dish from the oven</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>green beans</strong>, then return the dish to the oven, uncovered, for a further 10 min or until the green beans are tender</p><p>Once tender, squeeze over the<strong> </strong>juice of <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lime wedges</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style red duck curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-duck-curry-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Thai-style red duck curry </strong>over the<strong> rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
